{q:'Which is the oldest commercial bank in India still in operation?',o:['State Bank of India (as Imperial Bank, 1806)','Allahabad Bank','Punjab National Bank','Bank of India'],c:[0],e:'SBI traces its origins to the Bank of Calcutta (1806), making it the oldest commercial bank in India.'},
{q:'What is the penalty for bouncing a cheque under the Negotiable Instruments Act?',o:['Imprisonment up to 2 years or fine up to twice the cheque amount, or both','Rs 500 fine only','No penalty','1 year imprisonment only'],c:[0],e:'Under Section 138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, cheque bouncing can lead to imprisonment up to 2 years or fine up to twice the amount, or both.'},
{q:'What is the full form of EXIM Bank?',o:['Export Import Bank of India','Exchange and Import Bank','External Investment and Monetary Bank','Export Industrial Monetary Bank'],c:[0],e:'EXIM Bank stands for Export Import Bank of India, set up in 1982 to finance foreign trade.'},
{q:'What percentage of deposits must banks maintain as CRR?',o:['As per RBI notification (typically around 4-4.5%)','10%','2%','8%'],c:[0],e:'CRR is set by RBI and typically hovers around 4-4.5% of net demand and time liabilities.'},
{q:'What is a standing instruction in banking?',o:['An instruction to the bank to perform regular transactions automatically','A one-time transfer instruction','A verbal instruction to the manager','A complaint to the bank'],c:[0],e:'A standing instruction is an order given to the bank to make regular payments or transfers automatically.'},
{q:'Who appoints the RBI Governor?',o:['The Central Government (Government of India)','The Parliament','The Supreme Court','The RBI Board'],c:[0],e:'The RBI Governor is appointed by the Central Government of India.'},
{q:'What is a PPF account?',o:['Public Provident Fund — a long-term savings scheme','Personal Pension Fund','Private Provident Fund','Public Payment Fund'],c:[0],e:'PPF (Public Provident Fund) is a government-backed long-term savings scheme with tax benefits.'},
{q:'What is the lock-in period for a PPF account?',o:['15 years','10 years','5 years','20 years'],c:[0],e:'A PPF account has a lock-in period of 15 years, extendable in blocks of 5 years.'},
{q:'What is white label ATM?',o:['ATM set up and operated by non-banking entities','ATM operated by RBI','ATM inside a bank branch','ATM for international transactions only'],c:[0],e:'White label ATMs are set up, owned, and operated by non-banking entities (like Tata Communications for Indicash).'},
{q:'What is the tagline of Bank of Baroda?',o:['India\'s International Bank','The Banker to Every Indian','Good People to Bank With','Prosperity for All'],c:[0],e:'Bank of Baroda uses the tagline "India\'s International Bank".'},
{q:'What is e-KYC?',o:['Electronic Know Your Customer using Aadhaar-based verification','Extended KYC documents','Emergency KYC process','External KYC by a third party'],c:[0],e:'e-KYC is electronic verification of customer identity using Aadhaar-based biometric or OTP authentication.'},
{q:'Which of these is a payment bank?',o:['Paytm Payments Bank','HDFC Bank','ICICI Bank','Axis Bank'],c:[0],e:'Paytm Payments Bank is a payments bank licensed by RBI; HDFC, ICICI, and Axis are commercial banks.'},
{q:'What is the maximum balance a payments bank can hold per customer?',o:['Rs 2 lakh','Rs 1 lakh','Rs 5 lakh','Rs 50,000'],c:[0],e:'Payments banks can hold a maximum balance of Rs 2 lakh per individual customer.'},
{q:'What is the full form of NPA?',o:['Non-Performing Asset','Non-Productive Account','Net Profit Assessment','New Payment Arrangement'],c:[0],e:'NPA stands for Non-Performing Asset, a loan or advance where repayment is overdue.'},
{q:'In which year was PMJDY (Jan Dhan Yojana) launched?',o:['2014','2015','2016','2013'],c:[0],e:'Pradhan Mantri Jan Dhan Yojana was launched on August 28, 2014.'},
{q:'What is a bank\'s fiscal year in India?',o:['April 1 to March 31','January 1 to December 31','July 1 to June 30','October 1 to September 30'],c:[0],e:'The fiscal year in India, including for banks, runs from April 1 to March 31.'},
{q:'What is a Scheduled Bank?',o:['A bank listed in the Second Schedule of the RBI Act 1934','Any bank with a schedule of charges','A bank open on all days','A government-owned bank only'],c:[0],e:'A Scheduled Bank is one included in the Second Schedule of the RBI Act 1934, meeting criteria like minimum paid-up capital of Rs 5 lakh.'}
